  "prompt": "My heartrate is 60 beats per minute is that good or bad?",
  "response": "A resting heart rate of 60 beats per minute (bpm) is generally considered normal and can be a sign of good cardiovascular fitness, especially if you are an athlete or physically active. The normal resting heart rate for adults typically ranges from 60 to 100 bpm. \n\nHowever, what is considered \"good\" or \"bad\" can vary depending on individual circumstances, including your age, fitness level, and overall health. If you have any concerns about your heart rate or other aspects of your health, it is advisable to consult a healthcare professional for personalized advice.",
